SYNOPSIS
    int P_VALUE  "Value"

    int Set(P_VALUE, int value)
    int Query(P_VALUE)
      or
    int SetValue(int value)
    int QueryValue()

DESCRIPTION
    The value of the object, counted in copper coins.

EXAMPLE
    Set(P_VALUE, 23);

AVAILABILITY
    Include: <properties.h>

    Availability: /std/thing(/description) and descendants.

SEE ALSO
    thing(S), money(lib)
